Final states with hadronically decaying tau leptons are an important part of the ATLAS physics program. Examples are measurements of Standard Model processes [2–6], Higgs boson searches [7], searches for new physics such as Higgs bosons in models with extended Higgs sectors [8–10], supersymmetry (SUSY) [11–13], heavy gauge bosons [14] and leptoquarks [15]. This places strong requirements on the τhad-vis\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
