				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\tau _{\mathrm{had}{\text {-}}\mathrm{vis}}}$$\end{document}) two main criteria are applied: isolation at L12, and full tau identification at the HLT. The isolation requirement is dropped for the intermediate threshold version, and both criteria are dropped in favour of a looser (more than 95 % efficient), non-isolated trigger for the version with the highest thresholds.

