The chosen tag-and-probe approach consists of selecting events triggered by the presence of a lepton (tag) and containing a hadronically decaying tau lepton candidate (probe) in the final state and extracting the efficiencies directly from the number of reconstructed τhad-vis\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
